TI  - THE CONTRIBUTION OF REMOTE SENSING IN HIGHLIGHTING THE RESILIENCE OF RANGELANDS THROUGH INDICATORS OF LAND SURFACE TEMPERATURE AND THE NORMALIZED DIFFERENCE VEGETATION INDEX IN THE TIHAMA ALLUVIAL PLAIN
